13/01/2005
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- EUFOR Commander Major General David Leakey and the Bosniak and Croat members of the BiH presidency, Sulejman Tihic and Dragan Covic, met to discuss security and co-operation issues Wednesday (12 January). 
They agreed that accelerated defence and police reforms, combating organised crime and full co-operation with the UN war crimes tribunal are the top priorities.
In other news Wednesday, EUFOR transferred control over part of the infrastructure of Mostar Airport to municipal authorities. 
Talks are also under way on transferring airport fuel-storing facilities to muncipal control.
Also Wednesday, the local newspaper Glas Srpski published an article quoting High Representative Paddy Ashdown. 
He warned that RS leaders must no longer fail to meet their promises, especially those regarding war crimes co-operation and defence reforms. 
(Fena, PBS BiH, Pincom.info, OHR Web site, RTRS, NTV Hayat - 12/01/05)
